Thuso Mbedu, nominated for best performance by an actress in Is'thunzi attends the 45th International Emmy Awards at New York Hilton on November 20, 2017 in New York City. JOHANNESBURG - This weekend has been one of pride for South Africa as we celebrate our star actress Thuso Mbedu. She has captured hearts in her role as Cora Randall in ‘Underground Railroad’, a series currently streaming on Amazon Prime. READ: Thuso Mbedu to star alongside Viola Davis in new film Among those gushing over Mbedu’s phenomenal talent is the Queen of Talk, Oprah Winfrey. She’s shown love to our very own on Instagram, saying she gave the performance of a lifetime and that great things are coming her way. Winfrey also urged fans to pace themselves as they watch the show.